			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hmm - wouldnt be the way I'd do it.
<br />

<br />
This would be my method. (Or more acurately is my method)
<br />

<br />
Camp the bazaar - 
<br />

<br />
get a tash orb 
<br />

<br />
get some of the following - rusty spiked shoulderpads, 2x adamantite bands, astral leggings, astral cloak or some gloves I have forgotten the name of. Basically a good neg MR set.
<br />

<br />
Head to veksar highborn area and find a highborn. Charm it. Hand it the orb, fd and let it reset. Now find another highborn and charm it, hand it all the neg mr gear. Haste it. Set it on the first highborn - slow it, dot it watch it die etc. It should proc tash on your pet. Loot orb from first highborn.
<br />

<br />
You pet now has tash on it and neg MR gear bringing it to maybe -70 mr or even more. Charm will be very stable. Your pet is also a killing machine. BUT - do not let it die - you will lose all your gear.
<br />

<br />
When tash wears off fd and let your pet reset - find a mob to give the orb to and repeat. If charm breaks dont be a hero - fd an d let em reset. A hasted highborn is not to be messed with.
<br />

<br />
When you are done killing - kill your pet - either by charming a different mob or by normal pet tanking. Loot all your neg mr gear for the next time.
<br />

<br />
With your HP / gear keep fs up on yourself ALL the time. Virtue wouldnt be a bad idea either - particularly on your first go at it. Work on defensive aa's as a priority if you intend to make charming a full time occupation.
<br />

<br />
Once you have the hang of veksar try tactics for a change. I dont really like charming in Chard B TBH - I'd pet tank there.
<br />

<br />
Enjoy.
<br />

<br />
EDIT : When you are pushing 5k hp unbuffed like Needeep feel free to use his method. In the mean time dont go tanking highborns, slowed or otherwise.
<br />

<br />
EDIT 2.0 : Forget root in veksar - everything summons.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
